challenge Folder/Package Organization {
description
 Real-world domains are naturally "hypergraphs"
  but folder systems force them into strict "hierarchies"
 This forced translation leads to missing logic and lost relationships
 Therefore
  the best approach is to keep structures in a "single flat layer"
  and group items dynamically using properties like tags or search filter
priority schema (when folders are required) follow a strict directional flow
 source → target
 parent → child
 abstract → concrete
 general → unique
examples
 user1 / transfer / user2 # source → target
 tree / node / leaf       # parent → child
 user / name / first      # abstract → concrete
 animal / cat / jack      # general → unique
conclusion
 A directory, route, or folder is simply an aggregator of data
 Therefore, we need a way to:
  describe everything in a convenient relative model
  describe everything in a hierarchy using atomic and compound blocks
